  &lt;/figure&gt;
      &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the session continued, an engaging conversation took place around how the data stored within the ALSET Data Lake (ADL) can be used to help students surmount the challenges they face as NUS students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kevin emphasised that the synthetic data ALSET makes accessible to students only mimics the real data found in the ADL and is not real. However, the synthetic data is characteristic of the types of data NUS captures about its students. Accessing the synthetic data set places students in a good position to take action and find solutions to the challenges they encounter on campus. To demonstrate this, Kevin engaged the students in a quick data-driven decision making exercise.&lt;/p&gt;
