&lt;em&gt;Shun works at the ALSET Translation Research Unit as a Research Assistant. Besides writing code in the day, he likes attending meetups and taking long walks.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[From Game-based Learning to Game Creation @ Talk.js]]></title><description><![CDATA[Speaking to a group of developers attending the monthly Talk.js meetup at downtown Viki Rakuten Office, Prof Boesch introduced them to ALSET…]]></description><link>http://nus.edu.sg/alset/public//blog/13feb19talkJS/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">http://nus.edu.sg/alset/public//blog/13feb19talkJS/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 13 Feb 2019 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;Speaking to a group of developers attending the monthly Talk.js meetup at downtown Viki Rakuten Office, Prof Boesch introduced them to ALSET&apos;s work in nurturing young coders through Game-based Learning. After describing the coding platform CodeCombat, he went on to share about how many students experience their first time writing code through CodeCombat.&lt;/p&gt;
